e529ec69-79c0-4104-8976-34eda08d3d40.6ea96c92-de65-4b11-9ba6-d44400cf381f.description=

Synopsis\:
  This flow creates the zone to all AliasLif (multiple) to netapphost (multiple), cfgsave, cfgadd, and runs nszonemember output information.

1) Check for Nulls, init vars
2) Connect to HPNA (JRAS or HPNA), run nszonemember, zonecreate, etc, cfgsave, cfgadd...
3) Output success/failure and new alias info.

"Mandatory" (checkForNull) Inputs\:
hostalias_list - host
netapplif_list - lifs to connect to host

Results\:
 flowOutput -new alias information, XML format.

Responses\:
failure - Either couldn't connect to device, or 1 or more commands failed against ${deviceIP}
success - Ran all commands successfully against ${deviceIP}

e529ec69-79c0-4104-8976-34eda08d3d40.8a490df8-6c9d-4b31-9c67-175053474eb1.description=Attempts acquisition of a lock with an id given by the value of the lockId input. 
Inputs\:
   lockId - the id of the lock, maximum 255 characters.

Responses\:
   success - if the lock has been successfully acquired.
   failure - if the lock has already been acquired.

Result\:
   there are no results.

Notes\:

1) The operation does not block waiting for a lock to become available.

2) The locks acquired by this operation are not reentrant. This means that 
   once a lock is acquired by a run, all subsequent attempts at acquiring 
   the same lock by the same run (or any other run) will fail.

3) Once a run terminates, all the locks that were acquired during its execution
   are automatically released.

e529ec69-79c0-4104-8976-34eda08d3d40.description=
Summary
 - Main handling flow for zoning. 
To run this manually using zoning low-level flows.  Use the following logic, that buildZoning uses\:

Zoning End-To-End DEV test\: dryRun and Example Output\:
	1. Prework\:
	  - translateCase of dataCenterSearch to UPPER\: Ensure ZZ preamble on dataCenterSearch input.
	  - translateCase of custWwwpnList and NtapLifWwpnList to lower.  Verify regex format of WWPN is accurate.

	2. Run getBrocadesByDataCenter (UUID\: fbcf5f44-cc0f-4305-8bcb-af2b6a0839fd).  Got brocades for ZZSL7 (via OCI, no Brocade interaction)
                        via OCI Webservice
                     Output Example. 10.12.61.155,10.12.61.158

	3. Run flow getFabricsByDataCenterSwitches (UUID\: 52557e46-5a6f-4d73-afa4-8fe9038098f6) to get Fabrics and exampleIPs for each fabric found in ZZSL7/
                                 Note\: This flow determines FID and activeConfig, with following Logic\:
                                     - If virtualFabricsEnabled, then only 1 FID zoning\:ON\!\!
                                     - 1 activeConfig zonign config on switch (US and UK Both).  We will use presence of active zoning config, during discovery.
                                 Output Example\:
		1. 10.12.61.155,10.12.61.226,10.12.61.11,10.12.61.156
		2. brfs_001A_060810A,brfs_A_061009,brfs_004B_061009,brfs_002B_060810B
                                           3. ,,,

	4. Run flow searchBrocadesByAliasOrWwpn (UUID\: 5210fa51-93eb-4a56-b71b-a504cce94da3) Against NTAPlifNameList and custHostnameList.
		1. Use localOnly\=False in payload.
		2. Use  as input from step 3 above.
		3. Determine which aliases already exist, and on which .  CASE SENSITIVE ALIAS NAMES\!

	5. For Every Alias that DOES NOT EXIST (internal flow\: buildAlicreates)\:
		1. Run searchBrocadesByAliasOrWwpn  (UUID\: 5210fa51-93eb-4a56-b71b-a504cce94da3) on each WWPN with a non-existant alias pair.
                                              - Run with inputs\: localOnly\=False, same .
		2. Run createAlias (UUID\: aa1dd26c-9bb9-467e-8bb3-c07371e2d71b) foreach WWPN, it’s alias-pair, on  where WWPN was found.
		   - Note\: If WWPN is not found, End-to-End test method fails.
		   - Logic Note\: Will loop through full list of WWPNs before trying to execute first createAlias

	6. Once ALL Aliases exist on BROCADEs (pre-existing, or recently created with createAlias)\:
		1. run createZones (UUID\: a6806cae-a986-44b7-87a1-8fbaf5a2b980)
                                            Inputs\:
                                              - NTAP and CUST Aliases, for that fabric/IP, based on your searchByAlias (pre-existing aliases) or searchByWwpn (recently created) outputs.




Flow Inputs\:
 NOTE\: NameLists are case sensitive, and specific\!  Example\: if "alias1" already exists on fabric, and flow input NTAPlifNameList or custHostnameList\= "Alias1" would not find "alias1" and will create new "Alias1"\!

 - NTAPlifNameList / NTAPlifWwpnList\:
    - NTAP vserver EXPECTED Alias and WWPN pairing in the dataCenter somewhere.
                S603107SL7NAS01_03_0c
                20\:02\:00\:a0\:98\:13\:0a\:76
Where NTAP data comes from\:
1) Flow to get already-connected NTAP-to-CUST hostname/wwpns\: getVserverByHostInitiatorWwn (XML below correspond to getByHostInitatior) 
2) Need flow to get wwpn's where not plumbed through (collect all)  -- getSanLifListByVserver Outputs\: lifAliasName, wwpn, node?


 - custHostnameList / custWwpnList
    - Inputs come from TDC
    - Cust Alias and WWPN pairing in the same dataCenter (and same fabric, hopefully).
                    
                        10\:00\:00\:00\:c9\:6e\:48\:ba
                        
                            sl7stgsrv4
                            SL7STGSRV4_1
                        
                    

 - dataCenterSearch\: dataCenter to search for Alias and WWPNs, and create Alias and Zones on a fabric within.  Requires ZZ Preamble\!


Output\:
 flowOutput\: output from createAliasRas, and createZoneRas, with wrapped results for each exampleIP/fabricIP
 flowLoggerE2E\: Decision logic / flowLogger for flow.
e529ec69-79c0-4104-8976-34eda08d3d40.e4a39dd5-39b0-4fe8-bbcc-ac2abe36b327.description=Attempts to acquire the specified lock, and sleeps until the lock is available. 
Inputs\:
   lockId - the id of the lock, maximum 255 characters.
   timeout - The maximum number of seconds this flow will run for.
  seconds - The number of seconds to sleep for between each attempt at acquiring the lock.

Responses\:
   success - if the lock has been successfully acquired.
   failure - if the lock could not be acquired.

Result\:
   Code - 0 if the operation succeeds, 1 otherwise.

Notes\:
1) The locks acquired by this operation are not reentrant. This means that 
   once a lock is acquired by a run, all subsequent attempts at acquiring 
   the same lock by the same run (or any other run) will fail.

2) Once a run terminates, all the locks that were acquired during its execution
   are automatically released.

e529ec69-79c0-4104-8976-34eda08d3d40.e7f4fc6b-4cf6-4e64-bff9-8bb3d87ab8ed.description=
Synopsis

 This flow\:
1. Finds Brocade sanSwitches in DEV,QA,PROD based on dataCenterSearch input (Dev only supports dataCenterSearch\="")
2. Flow then builds IP (and if inUK, builds domainId/FID corresponding list too)
3. Flow runs getAliasByPatternMatch in parallel (multi-instance), and builds success/fail list of IPs (update\: and now activeconfig/fabric info too)
4. Reports brocade/alias/wwpn if found, or error if cannot connect to IP, for each IP in OCI.

Inputs

    dataCenterSearch - report only IPs/domainIds matching the datacenter (requires ZZ preamble).  DEV only supports NULL, as OCI does not use domainId information.

    patternToMatch - grep alias to find on each sanSwitch

    searchDomainId - should we search each FID on brocade? (is inUK?)

Results

    flowStatus - Found alias/matchingWwpn on each Brocade if found, and any issue IPs if cant connect

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
